After installing the Gluster Native Client, you need to mount Gluster
volumes to access data. There are two methods you can choose:

*
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Gluster_3.2:_Manually_Mounting_Volumes[Manually
Mounting Volumes]
*
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Gluster_3.2:_Automatically_Mounting_Volumes[Automatically
Mounting Volumes]

After mounting a volume, you can test the mounted volume using the
procedure described in
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Gluster_3.2:_Testing_Mounted_Volumes[Testing
Mounted Volumes].

*Note:* Server names selected during creation of Volumes should be
resolvable in the client machine. You can use appropriate /etc/hosts
entries or DNS server to resolve server names to IP addresses.

